</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1317,1697,1722]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,833,1902]" box="[199,1317,1697,1722]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1697,1722]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[360,444,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURE 42" captionStartId="85.[151,260,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,199,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[151,1436,193,1546]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="FIGURE 42. Distribution map of Brachygluta seri species-group and Brachygluta mormon species-group. A: Brachygluta chisos Sabella. B: Brachygluta klamath Bückle. C: Brachygluta cochimi Bückle. D: Brachygluta seri Chandler." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288098/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Fig. 
<number box="[413,444,1698,1722]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
A). This species is known only from western Texas (Big Bend National Park).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,833,1902]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1733,1758]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Comments.</emphasis>
This species shares with 
<taxonomicName box="[630,731,1733,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiowa">
<emphasis box="[630,731,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">B. kiowa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the indistinct/flattened/impressed roughened area in the basal portion of the disc of tergite 
<number box="[483,499,1770,1794]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" value="2.0">2</number>
, but in 
<taxonomicName box="[589,692,1769,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chisos">
<emphasis box="[589,692,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">B. chisos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this area is narrower and extends only to the middle of the disc, while in 
<taxonomicName box="[250,349,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiowa">
<emphasis box="[250,349,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">B. kiowa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it extends nearly the length of the tergite and two impressions are often distinct at the middle of this area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1142,1877,1902]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,833,1902]" box="[199,1142,1877,1902]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1877,1902]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is that of one of the indigenous groups known from this area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
